cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automatic segmentation of medical images using deep learning algorithms. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an approach that trains several neural networks on subgroups of data belonging to different segmentation variations separately. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses deep learning algorithms to improve the quality and clinical acceptance of automatic segmentation methods. 
4. cs.Medical Imaging is a relevant category as the paper deals with medical image segmentation. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses a genetic algorithm to search for the best data partition.
